  "origin": {
    "question": "Problem 17.8 (a) An observer (not necessarily freely-falling) orbits a Kerr black hole in the equatorial $(\\theta = \\pi /2)$ plane.\\n(a) Let his orbit be at constant $\\mathbf{r}$ . Define $\\Omega = \\frac{\\mathrm{d}\\phi}{\\mathrm{d}t}$ to be his \"angular velocity relative to a distant stationary observer.\" In terms of $\\Omega$ , $\\mathbf{r}$ , $\\mathbf{M}$ , and $\\mathbf{a}$ , find $\\mathbf{u}^0$ , $\\mathbf{u}^\\phi$ , $\\mathbf{u}_0$ , $\\mathbf{u}_\\phi$ .",
    "answer": "$u^0 = \\\\left[ 1 - \\\\frac{2M}{r} - \\\\frac{4Ma}{r}\\\\Omega - \\\\left(r^2+a^2+\\\\frac{2Ma^2}{r}\\\\right)\\\\Omega^2 \\\\right]^{-1/2}$\\n$u^\\\\phi = \\\\Omega u^0$\\n$u_0 = \\\\left( \\\\frac{2M}{r} - 1 - \\\\frac{2Ma}{r}\\\\Omega \\\\right) u^0$\\n$u_\\\\phi = \\\\left( \\\\frac{2Ma}{r} + \\\\left(r^2+a^2+\\\\frac{2Ma^2}{r}\\\\right)\\\\Omega \\\\right) u^0$",
    "solution": "1. 观测者在赤道面 ($\\\\theta = \\\\pi/2$) 做定半径运动，故径向与极向速度分量为零：$u^r = 0, u^\\\\theta = 0$。四速度形式为 $u^\\\\mu = (u^0, 0, 0, u^\\\\phi)$。\\n2. 由角速度定义 $\\\\Omega = \\\\frac{d\\\\phi}{dt} = \\\\frac{u^\\\\phi}{u^0}$，直接得到关系式 $u^\\\\phi = \\\\Omega u^0$。\\n3. 应用四速度类时归一化条件 $g_{\\\\mu\\\\nu}u^\\\\mu u^\\\\nu = -1$。由于仅有 $t, \\\\phi$ 分量非零，方程简化为：\\n   $g_{tt}(u^0)^2 + 2g_{t\\\\phi}u^0 u^\\\\phi + g_{\\\\phi\\\\phi}(u^\\\\phi)^2 = -1$\\n   代入 $u^\\\\phi = \\\\Omega u^0$ 并提取公因子：\\n   $(u^0)^2 (g_{tt} + 2g_{t\\\\phi}\\\\Omega + g_{\\\\phi\\\\phi}\\\\Omega^2) = -1$\\n4. 解出逆变时间分量：\\n   $u^0 = \\\\left[ -(g_{tt} + 2g_{t\\\\phi}\\\\Omega + g_{\\\\phi\\\\phi}\\\\Omega^2) \\\\right]^{-1/2}$\\n   $u^\\\\phi = \\\\Omega u^0$\\n5. 将 Kerr 度规在 $\\\\theta=\\\\pi/2$ 处的分量代入：\\n   $g_{tt} = -(1-2M/r)$, $g_{t\\\\phi} = -2Ma/r$, $g_{\\\\phi\\\\phi} = r^2+a^2+2Ma^2/r$\\n   计算括号内表达式：\\n   $-(g_{tt} + 2g_{t\\\\phi}\\\\Omega + g_{\\\\phi\\\\phi}\\\\Omega^2) = 1 - \\\\frac{2M}{r} - \\\\frac{4Ma}{r}\\\\Omega - \\\\left(r^2+a^2+\\\\frac{2Ma^2}{r}\\\\right)\\\\Omega^2$\\n   即得 $u^0$ 的显式。\\n6. 利用度规下降指标求协变分量：\\n   $u_0 = g_{tt}u^0 + g_{t\\\\phi}u^\\\\phi = (g_{tt} + g_{t\\\\phi}\\\\Omega)u^0 = \\\\left( \\\\frac{2M}{r} - 1 - \\\\frac{2Ma}{r}\\\\Omega \\\\right) u^0$\\n   $u_\\\\phi = g_{t\\\\phi}u^0 + g_{\\\\phi\\\\phi}u^\\\\phi = (g_{t\\\\phi} + g_{\\\\phi\\\\phi}\\\\Omega)u^0 = \\\\left( \\\\frac{2Ma}{r} + \\\\left(r^2+a^2+\\\\frac{2Ma^2}{r}\\\\right)\\\\Omega \\\\right) u^0$"
  },
